cs.NI, cs.DB, cs.DC, cs.SE, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on the Internet of Things and the communication between sensors and cloud-based middleware. 
- cs.DB (Databases) is also likely as the paper discusses the management and processing of data generated by IoT devices. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is relevant as the paper addresses the challenge of processing data streams from multiple sensors. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is relevant as the paper proposes a tool for sensor discovery and configuration. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is less likely but still relevant as the paper discusses the challenge of managing and processing large amounts of data generated by IoT devices.
